dct_title_s: Flood Plain Boundaries, Loudoun County, VA 2008
dct_description_sm: The regulatory floodplain boundary reflects the limits of flooding resulting from a storm having an occurrence probability of 1%, identified as the 100 year storm.  The floodplain boundary was recompiled from the listed sources onto the County's 1:2400 scale maps with five foot interval topography.  This floodplain feature class contains polygon feature classes only.
